# Northside Intelligence — Sector 3 tool rules

## Scope
- Snippets only. Minimal diffs. No drive-by refactors.
- Match existing patterns in this repo before adding abstractions.

## Secrets & logging
- Never hardcode API keys, tokens, or webhook secrets.
- No `console.log` / `console.error` in app code. Return structured API errors.

## Supabase
- Table prefix: `replyflow_` (change prefix when forking).
- Always check `{ error }` on service-role writes (webhooks, usage updates).
- Read user `plan` from `replyflow_profiles` — never hardcode tier/plan in routes.

## Stripe
- Verify webhook signatures with `STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET`.
- Handle subscription lifecycle: paid → update plan; cancel/unpaid → `free`.

## Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router, TypeScript, Tailwind.
- No unnecessary packages.

## PRs
- Wait for JB approval before merging to `main`.

## Branding
- Favicon must use the tool logo (`src/app/icon.svg`), not the NI portal emblem.
- When hosted in the NI monorepo, also add `public/{tool}/icon.svg` and register `favicon` in `src/lib/sector3-registry.ts`.
